On Saturday, August 05, 2006, at 10:23AM, Bruce Stewart <bandi(-at-)mweb.co.za> wrote:

>I've just managed to find myself an old VDO tachometer for my '71 Bus ;-).
>It has what I think is a part number on the back: 230/98/1.  There are three
>terminals on the back (and one "blank" terminal).  What do I connect them
>to?  One must connect to the coil, one to ground, and one to a positive
>supply I think.  From left to right, the terminals are labelled "-12", (the
>blanked one is labelled "6"), "15" and "+".

I'm not sure about that one but the old style tachs, when looking at the back of the tach and the horizontal pins were 4-3-2-1, then the wiring was:

4 - Terminal 1 on coil
3 - GND
2 - 12V
1 - leave unused

